Hosted by Educational Outreach Director Indira Sukhraj, this featured 45-minute faculty workshop will cover being involved in the community, sharing your passion for STEM, age-targeted teaching tactics, and more!

Come participate live in IST-1001! This workshop will not be available virtually.

Register Now on Our Workshops Page

Hosted by Nick Stafford, this hour-long workshop is the first part of our PC Building trilogy and will teach you all about part compatibility, knowing your model numbers, planning a build on a budget, and more!

Come see it live in IST-1017 and on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by professor and industry expert Dr. Bruce Jacob, this featured hour-long faculty workshop will cover not only the thought processes necessary to get started with making and selling your own product, but also the process of design and iteration that will lead you to an end product people want to give you money for.

Come participate live in IST-1060 or on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by Amanda Coleman, this 30-minute workshop will teach you all about how to get started with Git, GitHub, and version control, plus the basics for working with a shared or evolving programming project!

Come see it live in IST-1064 and on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by professor and industry expert Dr. Balasubramaniyan Chandrasekaran, this featured hour-long faculty workshop will act as an introduction to Unix-based operating systems. He will cover how to get started, what you need to know, and the applications of this technology.

Come see it live on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by Nick Stafford, this hour-long workshop is the second part of our PC Building trilogy and will cover starting your build, testing parts, cable management, and so much more!

Come see it live in IST-1017 and on Teams!

Register Now on our Workshops Page

Hosted by professor and industry expert Dr. Balasubramaniyan Chandrasekaran, this featured hour-long faculty workshop will expand upon last season's Robot OS 101 by diving deeper into the operating systems embedded in a robotic system, from Linux distributions to robotics best practices, and applying that to real-world solutions. Anybody interested in embedded systems or robot autonomy should definitely see this workshop.

Come see it live on Teams!

Hosted by Derek Lower, this featured hour-long faculty workshop will discuss the importance of recreation beyond just "working out," as well as the pillars of wellness and how they contribute to your academic success.

Come participate live in IST-1017 or on Teams!

Hosted by Nick Stafford, this hour-long workshop is the third and final part of our PC Building trilogy, covering overclocking your CPU and GPU, storage management, bloatware removal, custom water cooling, and more!

Come see it live in IST-1017 and on Teams!
